@Lpr

Crosswords fine, but I agree about anagrams.  They are not in my wheelhouse, so the theme fills really made no sense to me.

I’m glad that many enjoyed the puzzle, but for me the theme was too elusive.

@Marshall Walthew
Hand up for PRANK (which interfered with crosses, but I was just so sure....!)
Same with 'bend in a pipe' and SANTA -- (we lived in Santa CLARA County, and there's always ANITA, MARIA, LUCIA, etc.)  Oh well.

@Chris

Premission granted to solve this like a themeless puzzle.  

That's what I did.  The phrases are easy to guess once you get enough crosses.

@Kevin

It's only natural that people would have preferences for different types of puzzles.  If we can talk about that without being rude or critical of the constructor, I don't see a problem with that.  

There's nothing wrong with the puzzle, and I think the constructor did a fine job, but it isn't my favorite type of Sunday puzzle.

@Brillo

The Sunday puzzle drops on Saturday evening, so you probably solved the Sunday early.
(You should recognize the difference quickly because the Saturday puzzle is 7 x 7.)

@Splat did you 

Did you go through it in list mode, which you can do if you're on your phone in the app. It makes it a lot easier to spot errors than going through the grid. 

 Also, did you make sure that you don't have any zeros accidentally substituting for Os?

